==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*blada-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[blad]] (Dutch [[blad]]), Old High German [[blat]] (German [[Blatt]] ‘leaf’), Old Norse [[blað]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /blæd/

===Noun===
'''blæd''' ''n''
# a [[leaf]]
# the broad flat part of a utensil (e.g. an [[oar]] or [[spade]])

